	Global sugar production for 2004/2005 for 110 countries was estimated to be 144 million tons. It is noteworthy that most of the sugar produced is consumed domestically and only about 25% is traded internationally with the top three sugar exporting countries, Brazil, Thailand and Australia accounting for almost 50% of world exports (Illovo, 2005). In addition to providing direct employment for over 300,00..." /><meta name="keywords" content=", science, technology, agriculture, ACP, development, rural development, rural, Africa, Pacific, Caribbean, S&amp;T, policy dialogue, agricultural development, scientific, research and development, technology, policy, science and technology for the development" />    

